data.text:
It’s the 1993 WWF SummerSlam Watch-Along edition of the Grenade. The Lex Express rolls into Auburn Hills as Lex Luger challenges Yokozuna for the WWF Title. Bret Hart looks to exact revenge for the Hart Family as he takes on Jerry “The King” Lawler. The Undertaker faces the Giant Gonzalez in a “Rest In Peace” Match. Intercontinental Champion Shawn Michaels defends against Mr. Perfect to determine the greatest IC Champ of all time. Tag Champs the Steiners defend against Jim Cornette’s Heavenly Bodies. Plus, Razor Ramon vs. The Million Dollar Man in Dibiase’s final WWF match, the new sensation 1-2-3 Kid goes up against IRS, 6-Man action involving the Smoking Gunns & Tatanka vs. The Headshrinkers & Bam Bam Bigelow, Ludvig Borga makes his PPV debut vs. Marty Jannetty, plus the debut of Joe Fowler, and much to the dismay of Bruce Hart… Doink the Clown makes a surprise appearance!

THE WWF SUMMERSLAM 1993 WATCH-ALONG

AUGUST 30th, 1993 Featuring…

WWF Champion Yokozuna vs. Lex Luger

Who is King of the Ring? Bret Hart vs. Jerry Lawler

IC Champion Shawn Michaels vs. Mr. Perfect

Tag Champions The Steiner Brothers vs. The Heavenly Bodies

Rest In Peace Match: The Undertaker vs. The Giant Gonzalez

Razor Ramon vs. “Million $ Man” Ted Dibiase

The 1-2-3 Kid vs. IRS

6-Man Tag: The Smoking Gunns & Tatanka vs. The Headshrinkers & Bam Bam Bigelow

Marty Jannetty vs. Ludvig Borga

Bonus action with Bret Hart vs, Doink the Clown!
